# Eris environment template — copy to `.env` and fill in REAL values on the GENERAL/OPEN node only.
#
#   cp .env.example .env      # the real .env is gitignored (.env / .env.* / *.env)
#
# ⚠️  IP / PATENT (SOVEREIGN) NODE: do NOT create a .env here. That node runs local-only with no
#     keys and no egress; the egress_guard fails closed if it can even reach the network. Keys and
#     cloud routing belong ONLY to the general node that never touches your IP/patent work.
#
# Never commit real values. The already-leaked-and-revoked keys live in git history forever; this
# template carries names only so a NEW key never reaches a commit.

# ── HuggingFace (benchmark dataset downloads) ────────────────────────────────
# Removes the "unauthenticated requests" warning + rate limits when load_dataset pulls FRAMES/QuALITY.
HF_TOKEN=hf_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ── Benchmark BARE arm (Arm A) ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Local Ollama (default) OR a cloud OpenAI-compatible endpoint (OpenRouter) for speed + model
# comparison. Swap ERIS_BENCH_MODEL to compare LLM choices (qwen vs llama vs claude …).
ERIS_BENCH_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
ERIS_BENCH_MODEL=qwen/qwen-2.5-72b-instruct
ERIS_BENCH_API_KEY=sk-or-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ── ATTRIBUTABLE run (the iron rule: isolate architecture-vs-bare) ────────────
# Set to 1 for a one-model run: the runner FORCES ERIS_BENCH_MODEL into every slot (specialists,
# gap-closing, synthesis, AND the bare arm) and turns hive-synth-cloud OFF — so the ONLY variable
# between the two arms is the Eris architecture, never the model. This OVERRIDES any stale `set`
# (e.g. a lingering ERIS_TIER_SYNTH=…claude… from a prior speed run), so it can't print '✗ MISMATCH'.
# Leave UNSET (or 0) for a normal speed run that uses the tiers below as-is.
# ERIS_BENCH_ATTRIBUTABLE=1

# ── Local model (the hive's default brain, and Ollama context window) ────────
ERIS_LOCAL_MODEL=qwen3:14b
# Ollama default context is ~4096 — too small for QuALITY/FRAMES passages; raise before serving.
OLLAMA_CONTEXT_LENGTH=22000

# ── Hive (Eris arm) → cloud via the gateway, for SPEED (OPEN work only) ───────
# When ERIS_GATEWAY_BASE_URL is set, the hive's open-sensitivity calls (~18-21/question) route to
# the gateway instead of local Ollama, with fail-closed fallback to local if the cloud is down.
# The tier names must be REAL model ids your endpoint serves (OpenRouter model slugs).
ERIS_GATEWAY_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
ERIS_GATEWAY_API_KEY=sk-or-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
ERIS_TIER_FREE=qwen/qwen-2.5-72b-instruct
ERIS_TIER_CHEAP=anthropic/claude-3.5-sonnet
ERIS_TIER_SYNTH=anthropic/claude-3.5-sonnet
ERIS_HIVE_SYNTH_CLOUD=1

# ── Optional cloud experts (deep_mediator escalation path) ───────────────────
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# GEMINI_API_KEY=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ── Field τ channel ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Canonical vorticity ∇ρ×∇θ is the default; set to 0 only to reach the legacy Laplacian proxy.
# ERIS_TAU_VORTICITY=1
